<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idbf1c31a8-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s10250"><num value="10250">§ 10250.</num><heading> Termination of Office</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Office shall cease to exist not later than 30 days after the date 7 years after <date date="1987-12-22">December 22, 1987</date>.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idbf1c31a9-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">(<ref href="/us/pl/97/425/tIV/s410">Pub. L. 97–425, title IV, § 410</ref>, as added <ref href="/us/pl/100/202/s101/d/tIII">Pub. L. 100–202, § 101(d) [title III]</ref>, <date date="1987-12-22">Dec. 22, 1987</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/101/1329-104">101 Stat. 1329–104</ref>, 1329–121; <ref href="/us/pl/100/203/tV/s5041">Pub. L. 100–203, title V, § 5041</ref>, <date date="1987-12-22">Dec. 22, 1987</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/101/1330-247">101 Stat. 1330–247</ref>; amended <ref href="/us/pl/102/486/tVIII/s802/a">Pub. L. 102–486, title VIII, § 802(a)</ref>, <date date="1992-10-24">Oct. 24, 1992</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/106/2923">106 Stat. 2923</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idbf1c31aa-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idbf1c31ab-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I76" topic="codification" id="idbf1c31ac-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Codification</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0"><ref href="/us/pl/100/202">Pub. L. 100–202</ref> and <ref href="/us/pl/100/203">Pub. L. 100–203</ref> added identical sections.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="idbf1c31ad-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1992—<ref href="/us/pl/102/486">Pub. L. 102–486</ref> substituted “7 years” for “5 years”.</p>
</note>
</notes>
